Survey Event Analysis Markdown

Jennie Eardley

06/06/2020

Analysis of the results of a survey about a sporting event held in Scotland.

Usual Residence of Attendees

The organisers are interested in reducing single car use are were interested in knowing about methods of travel both to and during the event

- It is evident that car use is the most popular method of travel - The relatively remote location of the event may have prevented attendees from using public transport

Accommodation

- Respondents stayed in 88 different cities, towns and villages in Scotland - The most popular locations were: Comrie, Crieff and Perth - 56% of respondents stayed in places with populations of under 500

- 49% of respondents stayed in self catering accommodation, they spent an average of 882 on accommodation - 18% stayed at the event campsite - Comrie Croft, they spent an average of 194 on accommodation

Digital Interaction with Event

- 34% of participants followed the event on Twitter and/or Facebook - 85% of those who engaged rated the quality as excellent or good

Actionable Points

  • Consider alternative transport options
  • Investigate increasing the availability of water
  • Review wifi availability
  • Consider accessibility of public transport to social events

Recommendations for Future Surveys

  • Ask for more specific areas in other UK
  • Supply more options for the respondents to select from drop down lists
  • Ask about Twitter and Facebook separately
  • Ask for ratings by day of event
